<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="658" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="58.[790,1381,613,1032]" pageId="58" pageNumber="658">
Different studies place it as sister to a clade including 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1046,727,756]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Batomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="58" pageNumber="658" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Batomys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1130,1265,727,756]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Crateromys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="58" pageNumber="658" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Crateromys</taxonomicName>
or to a clade including 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1138,766,795]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Batomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="58" pageNumber="658" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Batomys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heaney, Balete, Rickart, Veluz &amp; Jansa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1224,1375,766,795]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Musseromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="58" pageNumber="658" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Musseromys</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="658" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="658" targetBox="[1343,1347,2188,2213]" targetPageId="58">
